DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(85)90010-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842668590010X
AB  - This paper empirically investigates the effects on the weekly returns of almost 100 banking organizations of the December 1982 authorization of Super NOWs. Examination of excess returns around the announcement date suggests that the announcement of the Super NOWs had a statistically significant (and negative) effect and that the impact differed significantly by type of bank. While returns for money center banks were generally unaffected, excess returns for regional retail banks were highly significant.
ER  - 

