DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(85)90007-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842668590007X
AB  - The paper investigates the behavior of stock prices for a group of well established and newly emerging LDC securities markets. The results suggest the probability distributions to be consistent with a lognormal distribution with some securities exhibiting non-stationary variance. LDC markets, even though not as efficient as major DC markets, are quite comparable to the smaller European markets and the behavior of security prices as reported in this study appears to be generalizable for the heavily traded segments of LDC markets.
